18
00:02:01,555 --> 00:02:03,690
So lucky.

19
00:02:06,994 --> 00:02:07,895
Tae Jin Ah.

20
00:02:09,696 --> 00:02:10,898
My goodness.

21
00:02:13,834 --> 00:02:17,204
Is that man waiting for you?

22
00:02:17,871 --> 00:02:18,939
Probably.

23
00:02:20,440 --> 00:02:21,942
I will get going first.

24
00:02:25,812 --> 00:02:27,748
She isn't only good at cursing,

25
00:02:28,482 --> 00:02:31,051
but singing and dating as well.

26
00:02:31,051 --> 00:02:33,754
There's so much to learn from her.

27
00:02:38,559 --> 00:02:39,426
Now,

28
00:02:40,827 --> 00:02:43,664
why don't you prove yourself?

29
00:02:48,468 --> 00:02:49,903
Where do I start?

30
00:02:50,637 --> 00:02:51,538
Yes.

31
00:02:52,039 --> 00:02:55,642
Selling pots and all stainless bowls
at home...

32
00:02:55,642 --> 00:02:58,111
just to go to Tae Jin Ah's concert?

33
00:02:59,012 --> 00:03:00,247
What else?

34
00:03:00,247 --> 00:03:02,549
Right. That Kyung Tae or Dong Tae guy
from church.

35
00:03:02,549 --> 00:03:04,818
You went to ask him out.

36
00:03:05,285 --> 00:03:07,754
Then you farted in front of him...

37
00:03:07,754 --> 00:03:10,657
and cried for the next couple of days.

38
00:03:11,892 --> 00:03:13,060
There's more.

39
00:03:13,060 --> 00:03:14,094
Stop. That's enough.

40
00:03:25,606 --> 00:03:27,908
Gosh, you jerk.

41
00:03:27,908 --> 00:03:31,011
Do you know how much I was worried?
I thought you dropped dead on the street.

42
00:03:31,778 --> 00:03:33,480
You look well.

43
00:03:34,515 --> 00:03:36,216
Did you meet that taxi driver too?

44
00:03:43,023 --> 00:03:44,458
I'll tell you about it later.

45
00:03:49,696 --> 00:03:51,565
Good to meet you again.

46
00:03:51,899 --> 00:03:53,033
Ms. O Du Ri.

47
00:04:08,649 --> 00:04:09,583
Right.

48
00:04:10,617 --> 00:04:12,753
My name is Park Jun.

49
00:04:13,754 --> 00:04:16,356
What? Jun?

50
00:04:16,356 --> 00:04:17,958
My goodness.

51
00:04:17,958 --> 00:04:20,427
How ugly.

52
00:04:20,427 --> 00:04:23,397
Jun? Seriously.

53
00:04:24,731 --> 00:04:26,466
I can't believe you. Jun?

54
00:04:29,269 --> 00:04:31,138
Anyway, see you later.

55
00:04:33,073 --> 00:04:34,107
My goodness.

56
00:04:44,017 --> 00:04:46,753
Was Park Gap Yong that attractive?

57
00:04:48,622 --> 00:04:50,924
("Strange Sisters who rushed the stage
and showed a legendary performance")

58
00:04:50,924 --> 00:04:53,293
(The advent of true retro deities)

59
00:05:03,403 --> 00:05:04,705
What's your plan?

60
00:05:06,006 --> 00:05:08,709
An unexpected reaction
at an unexpected timing.

61
00:05:08,709 --> 00:05:10,277
I didn't see this coming.

62
00:05:10,611 --> 00:05:12,946
It's not like we can reveal they're
from our agency just for that reaction.

63
00:05:14,381 --> 00:05:16,383
In terms of marketing strategy,

64
00:05:16,917 --> 00:05:19,486
this is better than clumsy mysticism.

65
00:05:20,521 --> 00:05:23,056
- What?
- Regardless of our will, people are...

66
00:05:23,056 --> 00:05:25,659
paying attention to them,
and it's our job to take advantage of it.

67
00:05:28,462 --> 00:05:30,430
Let's prepare a press release first.

68
00:05:33,100 --> 00:05:35,669
Mother is back, but she's a bit...

69
00:05:35,669 --> 00:05:37,471
No, she's very weird.
You have to come home now.

70
00:05:40,874 --> 00:05:43,577
(Managing Director Office)

71
00:05:44,611 --> 00:05:47,014
That's all I can tell you.

72
00:05:47,748 --> 00:05:49,716
I'm not hurt,

73
00:05:51,618 --> 00:05:53,420
but I'm being forgetful.

74
00:05:53,987 --> 00:05:56,990
If I act weird, don't be startled.

75
00:05:59,026 --> 00:06:01,361
Of course. Don't worry.

76
00:06:01,828 --> 00:06:04,831
I like your new sophisticated look.

77
00:06:06,300 --> 00:06:08,035
But the way you speak...

78
00:06:08,035 --> 00:06:08,936
What about it?

79
00:06:09,269 --> 00:06:10,270
Pardon?

80
00:06:11,071 --> 00:06:13,240
Well, you used to speak in a dialect.

81
00:06:13,240 --> 00:06:15,442
I'm surprised
that you suddenly got rid of it.

82
00:06:16,476 --> 00:06:17,778
She always knew how to talk without it.

83
00:06:18,412 --> 00:06:20,347
Are you sure you're not hurt?

84
00:06:21,048 --> 00:06:23,283
Why? Are you even worried?

85
00:06:24,251 --> 00:06:27,955
Aside from the way you speak,
you look like a totally different person.

86
00:06:28,422 --> 00:06:30,023
Isn't that what you wanted?

87
00:06:36,029 --> 00:06:39,032
After the near-death experience,
the world seemed different.

88
00:06:39,700 --> 00:06:41,134
It kind of cleared my mind.

89
00:06:42,703 --> 00:06:44,404
Clear your mind.

90
00:06:45,305 --> 00:06:47,007
That's a good thing.

91
00:06:47,007 --> 00:06:48,041
Right, honey?

92
00:06:48,809 --> 00:06:53,013
I dedicated my life to you long enough.

93
00:06:54,181 --> 00:06:55,716
There is a limit to a mother's love.

94
00:06:57,551 --> 00:06:59,086
And I've exceeded the limit.

95
00:07:02,189 --> 00:07:05,125
From now on, it's give and take.

96
00:07:05,893 --> 00:07:09,196
No meddling and no replying.
Let's live our lives now.

97
00:07:11,865 --> 00:07:14,434
What? You got a problem?

98
00:07:26,547 --> 00:07:29,650
We need to take Mother to the hospital.

99
00:07:29,650 --> 00:07:31,451
She said she wasn't ill.

100
00:07:31,752 --> 00:07:34,488
She knew how to speak without a dialect?

101
00:07:35,088 --> 00:07:38,358
If a young woman speaks in a dialect
while running a restaurant,

102
00:07:38,358 --> 00:07:40,360
people would ignore her,
so she avoided using it.

103
00:07:41,261 --> 00:07:44,498
That's how meticulous
your mother-in-law is.

104
00:07:46,667 --> 00:07:49,369
Yet, "give and take"?

105
00:07:49,369 --> 00:07:51,438
Why is she using English
like someone else?

106
00:07:51,972 --> 00:07:54,208
How could you be so apathetic?

107
00:07:54,208 --> 00:07:57,110
She's been attending senior university
and English academy for a while...

108
00:07:57,110 --> 00:07:59,179
to avoid being a shame
to her smart daughter and granddaughter...

109
00:07:59,179 --> 00:08:02,316
for not knowing English.

110
00:08:02,916 --> 00:08:03,784
But...

111
00:08:04,651 --> 00:08:07,154
I've never seen her using it
with pride before.

112
00:08:07,788 --> 00:08:10,023
She seemed determined.

113
00:08:10,490 --> 00:08:11,425
Right?

114
00:08:11,825 --> 00:08:14,127
She's cutting us off, right?

115
00:08:14,127 --> 00:08:16,230
She's definitely not acting like herself.

116
00:08:16,830 --> 00:08:18,699
But it doesn't mean it's not her.

117
00:08:19,199 --> 00:08:21,101
Something clearly happened...

118
00:08:21,101 --> 00:08:23,737
Dedicated her life to me?

119
00:08:24,438 --> 00:08:26,707
She saw that right through.

120
00:08:28,008 --> 00:08:29,776
Actually this is better.

121
00:08:30,777 --> 00:08:32,779
Now we can talk.

122
00:08:33,347 --> 00:08:37,084
I don't know about that.
She said it's give and take.

123
00:08:37,084 --> 00:08:39,386
I'm worried she might want...

124
00:08:39,386 --> 00:08:40,721
the late rent...

125
00:08:40,721 --> 00:08:42,890
- The late rent?
- Shoot.

126
00:08:46,026 --> 00:08:47,561
Dang it.

127
00:09:10,217 --> 00:09:11,885
Is she really a mother of a daughter?

128
00:09:35,042 --> 00:09:36,210
What are you doing here?

129
00:09:41,348 --> 00:09:42,182
Mal Soon.

130
00:09:54,361 --> 00:09:57,931
Okay. I get that you came to me
because I'm your family.

131
00:09:59,066 --> 00:10:00,033
But...

132
00:10:01,902 --> 00:10:03,770
what the heck are you doing in my house...

133
00:10:04,538 --> 00:10:06,540
pretending to be me?

134
00:10:06,540 --> 00:10:08,809
And I made it clear...

135
00:10:09,243 --> 00:10:11,912
that our relationship was over a long ago.

136
00:10:11,912 --> 00:10:13,947
There's no end to family.

137
00:10:14,414 --> 00:10:15,949
Just because you don't want to see me,

138
00:10:15,949 --> 00:10:18,118
you think you can end the family
like that?

139
00:10:18,118 --> 00:10:20,420
It came this far
because I thought it was over.

140
00:10:21,688 --> 00:10:22,523
Every time...

141
00:10:23,490 --> 00:10:26,860
I think about a family,
it makes me furious.

142
00:10:30,197 --> 00:10:33,834
I don't know what you're thinking,
but let's end it here.

143
00:10:34,801 --> 00:10:36,470
- Leave.
- No.

144
00:10:37,938 --> 00:10:39,373
I can't do that.

145
00:10:39,873 --> 00:10:40,807
What?

146
00:10:40,807 --> 00:10:42,342
Now I know the life you had...

147
00:10:43,043 --> 00:10:44,711
and the life you have now.

148
00:10:44,711 --> 00:10:46,880
How can I possibly leave you after that?

149
00:10:47,915 --> 00:10:49,283
What are you saying?

150
00:10:51,018 --> 00:10:52,619
You'll need my help.

151
00:10:54,588 --> 00:10:55,589
What if I refuse?

152
00:10:58,692 --> 00:11:00,527
How are you going to kick me out?

153
00:11:01,962 --> 00:11:04,097
Tell them that you're O Mal Soon.

154
00:11:09,369 --> 00:11:10,971
Two heads are better than one.

155
00:11:12,606 --> 00:11:13,373
What?

156
00:11:13,373 --> 00:11:16,610
Two people working together is
better than one person.

157
00:11:17,244 --> 00:11:19,746
Leave hopeless O Mal Soon to me.

158
00:11:19,746 --> 00:11:21,014
Cherish your time.

159
00:11:21,748 --> 00:11:24,651
And enjoy it.

160
00:11:26,787 --> 00:11:29,356
What are you blabbering about in English?

161
00:11:29,923 --> 00:11:32,426
Do you think this riddle is funny?

162
00:11:36,230 --> 00:11:39,633
Are you being rude
to my mother-in-law again?

163
00:11:39,633 --> 00:11:40,534
No.

164
00:11:41,301 --> 00:11:42,536
I can...

165
00:11:43,237 --> 00:11:44,171
explain.

166
00:11:45,339 --> 00:11:47,975
My mother-in-law is
under my protection now.

167
00:11:47,975 --> 00:11:51,011
If you startle or bug my mother-in-law
one more time,

168
00:11:51,011 --> 00:11:53,914
I will be really furious.

169
00:11:54,515 --> 00:11:57,117
It's not that I don't know how to get mad.
I just don't get mad often.

170
00:11:57,784 --> 00:11:59,386
I don't care that you're a lady.

171
00:12:01,522 --> 00:12:02,789
This is frustrating.

172
00:12:05,726 --> 00:12:06,860
Anyway,

173
00:12:08,929 --> 00:12:10,430
I'll take care of it.

174
00:12:11,231 --> 00:12:15,669
How can you avoid my help under my roof?

175
00:12:28,582 --> 00:12:29,583
Okay.

176
00:12:30,317 --> 00:12:31,318
I will be...

177
00:12:32,886 --> 00:12:34,087
careful from now on.

178
00:12:40,394 --> 00:12:42,095
How dare you?

179
00:12:42,563 --> 00:12:44,598
Glaring those big eyes...

180
00:12:44,598 --> 00:12:46,533
at my mother-in-law?

181
00:12:49,203 --> 00:12:50,470
Mother, are you okay?

182
00:12:51,138 --> 00:12:53,774
We have an unfinished conversation.

183
00:12:54,641 --> 00:12:56,043
You better explain yourself well.

184
00:13:04,251 --> 00:13:05,352
Dang it.

185
00:13:05,686 --> 00:13:09,590
<i>The man in the yellow shirt</i>

186
00:13:11,191 --> 00:13:15,295
<i>That quiet man</i>

187
00:13:16,730 --> 00:13:20,868
<i>For some reason</i>

188
00:13:32,846 --> 00:13:34,081
Ae Sim.

189
00:13:35,549 --> 00:13:37,551
How many schedules today?

190
00:13:37,551 --> 00:13:39,753
Do I have to work all night long
like yesterday?

191
00:13:41,688 --> 00:13:42,856
I almost passed out.

192
00:13:42,856 --> 00:13:46,493
So why did you become a hit?

193
00:13:46,493 --> 00:13:48,929
From broadcasting stations to army camps.

194
00:13:48,929 --> 00:13:51,431
Everyone wants Kim Ae Sim.

195
00:13:51,431 --> 00:13:53,433
Even yellow fabric is sold out...

196
00:13:53,433 --> 00:13:55,903
in Dongdaemun Market.

197
00:13:57,004 --> 00:13:59,072
Come on. Let's go.

198
00:14:03,143 --> 00:14:04,111
You...

199
00:14:05,279 --> 00:14:06,246
What are you doing here?

200
00:14:06,246 --> 00:14:08,081
Did you just see the Grim Reaper?

201
00:14:09,316 --> 00:14:11,084
What's that look on your face?

202
00:14:11,518 --> 00:14:13,387
Excuse me, but who are you?

203
00:14:14,555 --> 00:14:15,889
A friend?

204
00:14:15,889 --> 00:14:16,823
A friend?

205
00:14:17,524 --> 00:14:18,559
Right.

206
00:14:19,126 --> 00:14:21,261
Even a thief is still a friend.

207
00:14:23,263 --> 00:14:25,432
She's a waitress at the bar
I used to go to.

208
00:14:26,366 --> 00:14:29,436
I don't know what it's about,
but I'm busy. I'll talk to you later.

209
00:14:31,872 --> 00:14:33,507
Let's talk.

210
00:14:39,413 --> 00:14:40,747
Why now?

211
00:14:43,450 --> 00:14:44,751
We have to leave in five.

212
00:14:53,861 --> 00:14:55,429
What are you pulling here?

213
00:14:55,796 --> 00:14:57,764
And what was that? A thief?

214
00:14:58,765 --> 00:15:01,935
If you're not a thief,
should I call you a robber?

215
00:15:01,935 --> 00:15:02,769
What?

216
00:15:02,769 --> 00:15:05,272
Your face is on every channel
in this land.

217
00:15:05,706 --> 00:15:07,741
I hear your voice even if I shut my eyes.

218
00:15:08,775 --> 00:15:13,013
Because of that,
someone can barely have a sip of water.

219
00:15:13,680 --> 00:15:15,516
Yet you have the guts to go to work?

220
00:15:16,817 --> 00:15:18,886
How can you be wearing this?

221
00:15:18,886 --> 00:15:20,587
This wasn't going to be yours anyway.

222
00:15:21,355 --> 00:15:23,690
- Face it.
- It was mine.

223
00:15:23,690 --> 00:15:25,225
Choon Ho gave it to me.

224
00:15:25,826 --> 00:15:27,794
When he saw me running around...

225
00:15:27,794 --> 00:15:30,564
with heavy beer mugs,

226
00:15:30,564 --> 00:15:33,233
I reminded him of a yellow chick
and bloomed forsythia.

227
00:15:33,767 --> 00:15:35,435
I reminded him of exciting...

228
00:15:35,435 --> 00:15:37,504
and throbbing lyrics.

229
00:15:39,273 --> 00:15:40,240
So what?

230
00:15:40,774 --> 00:15:44,144
You can't even tell
if that's music or bean sprouts.

231
00:15:47,214 --> 00:15:50,817
I met Choon Ho way before you did.

232
00:15:51,418 --> 00:15:55,255
Until you appeared, I was his muse.

233
00:15:57,191 --> 00:15:59,526
What? Muse?

234
00:16:01,061 --> 00:16:03,330
Everything's back to its place.

235
00:16:03,330 --> 00:16:05,832
Don't be so sad about a mere song.

236
00:16:05,832 --> 00:16:07,034
Live your life.

237
00:16:07,601 --> 00:16:09,102
And don't come back to me again.

238
00:16:09,102 --> 00:16:11,705
You think you only stole a song?

239
00:16:13,373 --> 00:16:14,975
You stole my dream and my life.

240
00:16:16,610 --> 00:16:19,913
That was the only thing...

241
00:16:20,714 --> 00:16:22,583
this uneducated and poor loner...

242
00:16:22,583 --> 00:16:24,451
liked, was good at,

243
00:16:24,451 --> 00:16:26,887
and the only reason to carry on.

244
00:16:26,887 --> 00:16:28,755
And that's what you stole from me!

245
00:16:31,225 --> 00:16:34,027
You gross me out.

246
00:16:37,030 --> 00:16:39,833
And that's not how you sing
"The Man in the Yellow Shirt."

247
00:16:41,335 --> 00:16:44,805
You're not supposed to stand firmly
and act all pretty when you sing it.

248
00:16:47,040 --> 00:16:48,475
Open your eyes softly,

249
00:16:48,942 --> 00:16:51,044
leave your body to the rhythm,

250
00:16:51,044 --> 00:16:53,213
and enjoy singing,

251
00:16:53,213 --> 00:16:56,750
so all listeners would dance.

252
00:16:56,750 --> 00:16:59,152
That's how you're supposed to sing it,
you wench.

253
00:17:05,826 --> 00:17:07,461
We're late. Let's go, Ae Sim.

254
00:17:35,189 --> 00:17:37,558
There's this suspicious girl.

255
00:17:38,225 --> 00:17:39,326
Will you look into her?

256
00:17:44,464 --> 00:17:45,866
What are you watching?

257
00:17:45,866 --> 00:17:48,502
It's Ha Na. We haven't seen her...

258
00:17:48,502 --> 00:17:50,671
smiling like this for years.

259
00:17:53,173 --> 00:17:54,775
My goodness.

260
00:17:59,046 --> 00:18:00,547
I don't see or hear...

261
00:18:02,382 --> 00:18:03,650
anything else.

262
00:18:05,118 --> 00:18:07,387
All I see is the big smile on her face.

263
00:18:50,964 --> 00:18:52,065
Father.

264
00:20:14,982 --> 00:20:16,283
(Missed Call, Chairwoman Kim)

265
00:20:34,201 --> 00:20:35,469
You're up early.

266
00:20:35,869 --> 00:20:36,970
Do you want some?

267
00:20:41,241 --> 00:20:43,377
Mother has...

268
00:20:43,377 --> 00:20:46,446
not only changed her style,
but her taste as well.

269
00:20:47,047 --> 00:20:49,116
It's coffee. Americano.

270
00:20:51,118 --> 00:20:53,987
I know that you've changed.

